 Kellerer's proof, we also prove simultaneously his result and ours\nin this case.-- If $\\mu$ is absolutely continuous in Wasserstein space P2(R)\nthen X is solution of a Benamou--Brenier transport problem with marginals\n$\\mu$t. Itprovides a Markov probabilistic representation of the continuity\nequation, unique in a certain sense.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 27 Apr 2018 13:59:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-30"}
